    {
      "id": "b67d4fa37a41f1d8831b8f720369ffedb2abbcef",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 11,
        "name": "Michael MacDonald",
        "email": "michael.macdonald@intel.com",
        "username": "mjmac",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-22 14:36:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI'm not crazy about the dependency on sudo for getting kernel-devel RPMs, but I understand that it may be the best option of many bad options, and that we need to get RHEL6 support landed.  Perhaps when CentOS6 becomes available this can be revisited with a more general solution that doesn't require sudo.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3d512e7fffd547e766cc95dd382bc9f5c3245f26",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 1,
        "name": "Robert Read",
        "email": "robert.read@intel.com",
        "username": "rread",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-22 15:40:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI agree with Mike - relying on sudo being available in the build slaves seems incorrect. Why are we doing this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
